full_title: PROBLEMATIC by ¥$, Kanye West & Ty Dolla $ign
title: PROBLEMATIC

description.plain:
“PROBLEMATIC,” alternatively known as “Murder Murder” and, according to some insiders, originally titled “Worship”, marks the fifteenth track of Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign’s collaborative album VULTURES 1. The song was first previewed on September 1, 2023, at Electric Picnic Festival in Dublin, Ireland where Ye previewed multiple unreleased songs to Steve Lacy backstage, including songs with Ty Dolla $ign and Young Thug, which is believed to have included their track “River”. The song was played in full on February 8, 2024, at the Chicago Vultures Listening Party and again the following day at the New York Vultures Listening Party on February 9, 2024.

The track showcases Ye’s return to soul samples, a style of production popularised in his earlier projects such as The College Dropout. This song, in particular, samples Jubilation’s “Spooky Booth”. Throughout the track, Ye speaks on the backlash he faced following his controversial statements in late 2022 whilst bragging about his influence on the music and fashion worlds.
